The paper deals with the analysis of communication systems and the design of power allocation over parallel channels, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the wideband regime, which is a topic covered in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of minimum-mean-squared error functions, which are commonly used in the fields of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Multimedia (cs.MM).
